The Commerce Club was Ahhhmazing! Top notch customer service. I went with a friend, who is a member, of the club. I took some kids on a field trip. The staff treated us like members. The food and the view of Atlanta was breathtaking. I had the chicken breast sandwich on ciabatta bread. It was very delicious. One of my kids said, "If this is heaven, I don't want to leave." I will definitely be back.

I held a USMC Reunion at this location.  Beautiful venue and the food was delicious.  Here were my issues:  1.  The table linen was incorrect, even after a picture was sent and they confirmed, it was still incorrect...  Centerpieces were designed to go with the linen specified. 2.  On more than 3 occasions, we had to get with the Manager to have staff fill water glasses.  There were other little things, but not worth mentioning.  The biggest issue was when it came to the service charge.  The Service Charge is based on all billable amounts, to include the portion to cover the F&B minimum.  Not only did the staff not earn a 22% tip on the F&B served, they most certainly did not earn it on the additional $4,000 charge to cover the F&B Minimum.  I don't think we will be having another event there.

The Commerce Club is a scam and by default Club Corp as a whole will never see me in one of their clubs again. For that, it was worth $415.

Absolutely breathtaking view. ⭐The Commerce club⭐ is a  private club located is the heart of downtown on the 49th floor  Of building 191 on peachtree street. Windows on 3 sides of the building Ensure a beautiful sunset or sunrise.  The club bost  private meetng rooms and office space is available makes it great for business meeting and lunch. There are 3 rather large  dining rooms. The food is absolutely delicious. On Friday night I have  steak and lobster.  The crawfish corn chowder  Always leave my mouth watering for more.  The rib eye steaks are fresh,  perfectly chosen  and cooked  to your perfection.  The wait staff is second to none. The poor rating is because of the poor food quality. We brought friends with us and we were embarrassed by the "rib-eye" steaks and the grouper. There was so much grizzle in the steaks, they were difficult to cut. We wondered if they were actually rib-eyes. The grouper was mushy. Yes, it's a beautiful setting and the staff was friendly and efficient but we've never paid so much for so little quality.
